          "name": "Match Jira user",
          "prompt": {
            "mode": "manual",
            "value": "You are given the name of a person who submitted a request: \"{{code.output.submitted_by_name}}\"\n\nBelow is a list of Jira users returned by a search:\n{{jiraFindUsers.output.results}}\n\nEach user has a `displayName` and `emailAddress`. Your job is to find the user who best matches the submitted name. Prefer users whose email contains the person's last name (e.g. if the name is \"Peter Crowder\", prefer peter.crowder@sumup.com). Prioritise @sumup.com email addresses over personal emails.\n\nReturn ONLY the raw `accountId` string of the best matching user in the `accountid` output field. Do not include backticks, quotes, or any other formatting — just the plain accountId value."
          },
